09:19.268 --> 09:20.468
(PLAYFUL GROWL)

09:20.469 --> 09:22.503
Housekeeping. Ignore it.

09:22.504 --> 09:25.472
- It's 11:00, doofus.
- Mm-hmm.

09:26.540 --> 09:28.276
(LOUD KNOCKING)

09:28.277 --> 09:30.211
That really isn't housekeeping.

09:30.212 --> 09:31.778
(SIGHS)

09:36.083 --> 09:38.653
- Sorry to interrupt.
- Angela.

09:38.654 --> 09:40.987
See you in court, you bastard.

09:50.064 --> 09:52.566
Looks like you got a late
start this morning, Dave.

09:52.567 --> 09:54.402
Long night. Not much sleep.

09:54.403 --> 09:57.171
Teenagers, huh? No, the kids are fine.

09:57.172 --> 09:59.473
I think.

09:59.474 --> 10:01.042
I didn't go home.

10:01.043 --> 10:03.644
Angie served me with
divorce papers last night.

10:03.645 --> 10:06.013
Oh, man. I had no idea.

10:06.014 --> 10:08.715
Could you believe it?

10:13.854 --> 10:15.856
New keyboards are pretty sweet, too.

10:15.857 --> 10:17.491
Yeah, just the right resistance.

10:17.492 --> 10:20.227
(MONITOR BEEPING)

10:20.228 --> 10:22.430
Teykovo and Kartaly lighting up.

10:22.431 --> 10:23.731
I've got Kozelsk

10:23.732 --> 10:25.499
and Yurya. Talbot, report.

10:25.500 --> 10:27.601
Dozens of launches across Russia.

10:27.602 --> 10:29.570
Get any warnings from FSB about tests?

10:29.571 --> 10:31.505
- No, sir.
- Anybody... anything on MOLINK?

10:31.506 --> 10:32.807
No reports, sir.

10:32.808 --> 10:34.175
SSPARS, report.

10:34.176 --> 10:36.210
Confirmation from Thule
and Fylingdales.

10:36.211 --> 10:37.912
More than a hundred so far.

10:37.913 --> 10:39.313
Not in range of Alaska yet.

10:39.314 --> 10:40.448
I have trajectory.

10:40.449 --> 10:43.884
Mainland U.S., coast
to coast, top to bottom.

10:43.885 --> 10:47.555
Get me CiC's crisis coordinator.

10:47.556 --> 10:49.757
(PHONE PLAYING ALARM TONE)

10:49.758 --> 10:53.160
- Soothing ring choice.
- It's STRATCOM.

10:53.161 --> 10:55.363
This is NSA Ellen Hill.

10:55.364 --> 10:57.298
DALTON: Do we have the Pentagon
War Room on the line?

10:57.299 --> 10:59.333
Yes, Mr. President.
General Nelson here.

10:59.334 --> 11:01.035
Ready to authenticate
the nuclear launch codes

11:01.036 --> 11:02.402
on your call.

11:07.708 --> 11:09.110
I'm ready for your
challenge code, General.

11:09.111 --> 11:12.546
Tango. Delta. Seven. Eight.

11:12.547 --> 11:15.282
Two. Two. Victor.

11:15.283 --> 11:19.520
November. Niner. Five. Eight. Two.

11:19.521 --> 11:21.588
Copy, sir. Your orders?

11:23.324 --> 11:26.427
DALTON: Zulu. Echo. Six.

11:26.428 --> 11:29.063
Two. Five.

11:29.064 --> 11:31.632
Eight.

11:31.633 --> 11:35.002
Confirming. Zulu. Echo.

11:35.003 --> 11:38.506
Six. Two. Five. Eight, sir.

11:38.507 --> 11:39.973
Over.

11:41.876 --> 11:43.711
Confirmed.

11:43.712 --> 11:45.880
NELSON: Copy, Mr. President.

11:45.881 --> 11:48.615
Godspeed, sir.

11:58.726 --> 12:00.861
(COMPUTER BEEPS)

12:00.862 --> 12:02.496
- General Nelson.
- What?

12:02.497 --> 12:04.098
Your security clearance
has been revoked

12:04.099 --> 12:06.267
under the Personnel
Reliability Program.

12:06.268 --> 12:07.501
We're at war, damn it.

12:07.502 --> 12:09.036
And you must leave the building.

12:09.037 --> 12:10.671
What the hell is this about?

12:10.672 --> 12:12.105
Your divorce, General.

12:19.380 --> 12:22.750
Captain Barnes. Yes, ma'am. Copy.

12:22.751 --> 12:25.286
The Pentagon War Room

12:25.287 --> 12:27.488
cannot issue the EAM
to launch control centers.

12:27.489 --> 12:28.722
- Since when?
- What the hell?

12:28.723 --> 12:29.649
Look, I'm sorry, sir,

12:29.650 --> 12:31.692
but you need to reissue
the order to STRATCOM.

12:31.693 --> 12:32.760
MCPHERSON: <i>Tango.</i>

12:32.761 --> 12:36.263
Delta. Seven. Eight. Two. Two.

12:36.264 --> 12:39.567
Victor. November. Niner.
Five. Eight. Two.

12:39.568 --> 12:40.801
MCPHERSON: Copy.

12:40.802 --> 12:42.936
Your orders, Mr. President?

12:54.815 --> 12:58.919
Zulu. Echo. Six. Two. Five. Eight.

12:58.920 --> 13:01.689
Confirming. Zulu. Echo.

13:01.690 --> 13:06.560
Six. Two. Five. Eight. Sir. Over.

13:06.561 --> 13:09.930
Confirmed. God bless, Colonel.

13:09.931 --> 13:12.699
Thank you, Mr. President.

13:25.779 --> 13:27.948
There's no turning back now.

13:27.949 --> 13:30.651
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

13:30.652 --> 13:32.753
- (ALARM BLARING)
- Here we go.

13:32.754 --> 13:34.955
Not a drill.

13:34.956 --> 13:37.057
Unlock launch keys.

13:37.058 --> 13:38.625
I agree.

13:50.371 --> 13:51.605
Alpha. Zulu.

13:51.606 --> 13:52.973
X-Ray.

13:52.974 --> 13:55.376
I have a match.

13:55.377 --> 13:58.078
Authentication confirmed.

13:58.079 --> 14:00.114
I agree.

14:00.115 --> 14:01.714
Belt up.

14:06.654 --> 14:09.722
Insert launch keys.

14:11.892 --> 14:13.160
ELIZABETH: <i>Hey!</i>

14:13.161 --> 14:15.262
Where is everybody?

14:15.263 --> 14:17.565
I'm going for a personal best here.

14:17.566 --> 14:18.666
- Ma'am.
- Huh?

14:18.667 --> 14:20.367
We have to get you off the premises.

14:20.368 --> 14:21.936
- Now.
- What's this about?

14:21.937 --> 14:23.571
Code Night Watch, ma'am.

14:23.572 --> 14:25.539
Okay, wait, hold on, my family.

14:25.540 --> 14:27.274
- What's going on?
- We're trying to reach the secretary.

14:27.275 --> 14:28.542
There's no reception in here.

14:28.543 --> 14:30.244
We have Mr. Jackson
on the line outside.

14:30.245 --> 14:32.645
Okay, um, I'll be right back.

14:33.881 --> 14:35.382
What the hell's going on?

14:35.383 --> 14:36.450
RUSSELL: It's real.

14:36.451 --> 14:38.552
The Russians launched
the kitchen sink.

14:38.553 --> 14:39.920
What?

14:39.921 --> 14:41.488
You should be heading
to Mount Weather.

14:41.489 --> 14:42.990
Wait. Where's the rest of the NSC?

14:42.991 --> 14:44.658
Aren't we advising POTUS
on countermeasures?

14:44.659 --> 14:45.793
RUSSELL: We already did.

14:45.794 --> 14:48.062
The president ordered
Major Attack Option One.

14:48.063 --> 14:49.196
It's done.

14:49.197 --> 14:52.766
Oh, my God. I...

14:52.767 --> 14:54.301
Bess, just go.

14:54.302 --> 14:55.569
ELIZABETH: Yeah.

14:55.570 --> 14:59.106
You take care, okay?

14:59.107 --> 15:01.408
We have a helicopter on top
of the Unified building.

15:01.409 --> 15:02.643
We have to hurry.

15:02.644 --> 15:04.812
No, no. I-I'm not, I'm not going.

15:04.813 --> 15:06.447
I'm-I'm gonna stay with my family.

15:06.448 --> 15:07.781
Ma'am?

15:07.782 --> 15:10.983
Try Deputy Cushing. Go.

15:14.989 --> 15:18.192
I'm trying to decide
if I should call Carol...

15:18.193 --> 15:19.826
and the boys.

15:21.895 --> 15:24.197
What's the point?

15:30.994 --> 15:33.829
<i>(ALARM BLARING)</i>

15:35.098 --> 15:37.566
There's no turning back now.

15:42.272 --> 15:44.706
Keep working. Man your stations.

15:47.977 --> 15:50.679
- Initiate Major Attack Option One.
- I agree.

15:55.084 --> 15:57.954
- Shut up.
- Stop coaching.

15:57.955 --> 15:59.922
Okay, wait, hold on, my family.

16:01.891 --> 16:03.259
Too much skill.

16:03.260 --> 16:06.295
Bess, just go, okay?

16:08.064 --> 16:10.399
Mid-course phase. Warheads detaching.

16:12.135 --> 16:13.802
Tracking more than 2,000.

16:16.306 --> 16:17.941
No, no! Abort! Abort!

16:17.942 --> 16:20.109
General Bradley...
Now! Send a new EAM aborting it!

16:20.110 --> 16:22.611
Do it! Oh, for God's sake.

16:24.948 --> 16:26.381
- Abort, abort.
- Come on.

16:39.262 --> 16:42.699
- Silo covers clear.
- Agreed.

16:42.700 --> 16:45.200
STEVIE: Oh, my God.

16:51.474 --> 16:53.176
Launch actions. Hands on keys.

16:53.177 --> 16:54.643
I agree.

16:56.846 --> 17:01.150
Fire on my mark. Three, two, one,

17:01.151 --> 17:03.418
- mark.
- (ALARM BEEPING)

17:13.296 --> 17:15.431
Ma'am.

17:15.432 --> 17:17.367
We're off Code Night Watch.

17:17.367 --> 17:19.068
All clear.

17:19.069 --> 17:21.436
Wait, that's... that's confirmed?

17:21.438 --> 17:22.605
Yes, ma'am.

17:22.606 --> 17:24.107
All clear.

17:24.108 --> 17:28.243
Thank you, Jimmy. Thank you.

17:28.244 --> 17:30.079
(SOBBING)

17:30.080 --> 17:33.082
Mom? Mom.

17:33.083 --> 17:34.450
Are you okay?

17:34.451 --> 17:37.086
Oh, I just got so light-headed.

17:37.087 --> 17:38.655
HENRY: Uh, she forgot to eat.

17:38.656 --> 17:40.618
So, Jace, just go get her a
pizza or something, okay?

17:40.619 --> 17:41.624
I need...

17:41.625 --> 17:42.825
- Eat, Mom.
- Okay, yeah.

17:42.826 --> 17:44.794
Okay. (CHUCKLES)

17:44.795 --> 17:47.797
STEVIE: You ready for this?

17:47.798 --> 17:50.032
(BOTH LAUGHING)

17:56.005 --> 17:57.340
Problem solved?

17:57.341 --> 17:59.809
He's not gonna like it.

17:59.810 --> 18:01.411
POTUS was head faked
into ordering Armageddon.

18:01.412 --> 18:03.479
Not gonna like it is
the least of your worries.

18:03.480 --> 18:07.417
I just had a nice chat
about organic juicing

18:07.418 --> 18:08.851
with my son in Santa Barbara,

18:08.852 --> 18:12.121
who I thought I was
never going to see again,

18:12.122 --> 18:14.324
so this better be good, Gordon.

18:14.325 --> 18:15.491
As you recall, sir,

18:15.492 --> 18:18.294
STRATCOM recently upgraded
its systems; hardware,

18:18.295 --> 18:19.327
software...

18:19.328 --> 18:21.230
Are you telling me this
was some kind of glitch?

18:21.231 --> 18:22.532
No, sir.

18:22.533 --> 18:24.200
Apparently, General Bradley
wanted to run a stress test

18:24.201 --> 18:25.335
on this new equipment

18:25.336 --> 18:26.769
to see how it would
interact with personnel.

18:26.770 --> 18:29.172
- A stress test?
- So he had his CTO

18:29.173 --> 18:32.909
upload a simulation
on the backup system

18:32.910 --> 18:35.178
at the end of his shift last night

18:35.179 --> 18:37.313
because he wasn't gonna
be in for the weekend.

18:37.314 --> 18:38.481
God forbid he be inconvenienced.

18:38.482 --> 18:39.782
DALTON: A simulation?

18:39.783 --> 18:42.251
I almost ended the world
because of a simulation?

18:42.252 --> 18:43.886
Bradley didn't inform staff.

18:43.887 --> 18:45.989
He wanted them to believe it was real.

18:45.990 --> 18:48.324
Planned on running it
when he got back in,

18:48.325 --> 18:50.927
but the primary system
unexpectedly failed

18:50.928 --> 18:52.662
and the backup came on seamlessly,

18:52.663 --> 18:55.131
so no one in the GOC knew.

18:55.132 --> 18:56.933
Pretty convincing simulation.

18:56.934 --> 18:58.835
I think that's the point.

18:58.836 --> 18:59.936
Fire Bradley.

18:59.937 --> 19:01.704
I've already relieved him
of duty, sir.

19:01.705 --> 19:02.905
HILL: Didn't we change our procedures

19:02.906 --> 19:05.108
on simulations after '79?

19:05.109 --> 19:06.509
Supposed to be on computers off-site.

19:06.510 --> 19:10.380
Like many four stars,
Bradley doesn't lack confidence.

19:10.381 --> 19:11.714
He ignored the rule.

19:11.715 --> 19:13.616
And what if General Nelson
didn't have clearance issues?

19:13.617 --> 19:16.653
Would Bradley have arrived
in time to abort the launches?

19:16.654 --> 19:19.756
No, sir. It slowed the order
by almost two minutes.

19:19.757 --> 19:21.057
We were down to the wire

19:21.058 --> 19:22.659
in a few of our
launch control centers.

19:22.660 --> 19:26.329
So the world was saved
by a philandering general.

19:26.330 --> 19:28.097
Maybe his mistress should get a medal.

19:28.098 --> 19:30.299
I've ordered a review
of our alert procedures, sir,

19:30.300 --> 19:32.402
- system wide.
- Well,

19:32.403 --> 19:34.537
that ought to take care of it.

19:34.538 --> 19:35.805
We've been on this posture

19:35.806 --> 19:40.009
for over 50 years,
what else do we need to know?

19:40.010 --> 19:42.812
- What are you getting at, Bess?
- Isn't the problem

19:42.813 --> 19:45.048
the policy itself?

19:45.049 --> 19:48.885
Being on hair-trigger alert
to order the destruction

19:48.886 --> 19:50.353
- of the planet.
- HILL: Like you said,

19:50.354 --> 19:51.587
it's worked for 50 years.

19:51.588 --> 19:53.421
I didn't say it's worked.

19:54.357 --> 19:56.926
It's more like...

19:56.927 --> 19:58.161
we've been lucky.

19:58.162 --> 20:00.203
The Russians are on ready-alert, too.

20:00.204 --> 20:03.066
What choice do we have,
but to counterbalance?

20:03.067 --> 20:04.701
De-alert our silos.

20:04.702 --> 20:06.469
And how exactly

20:06.470 --> 20:07.537
would we do that?

20:07.538 --> 20:09.505
Remove the warheads from the missiles.

20:09.506 --> 20:11.207
So it'd take several hours

20:11.208 --> 20:13.142
or days to rearm. If we de-alert

20:13.143 --> 20:15.178
our ICBMs, it would put
too much pressure

20:15.179 --> 20:16.813
on the other forces
of the nuclear triad.

20:16.814 --> 20:19.882
- There's a reason a stool has three legs.
- Our subs become vulnerable.

20:19.883 --> 20:21.718
If there's a problem
with our bombers...

20:21.719 --> 20:24.970
We have 14 stealth subs,
each with more than enough

20:24.971 --> 20:28.007
warheads to destroy Russia.

20:28.008 --> 20:30.910
We have a hundred
nuclear-armed bombers.

20:30.911 --> 20:34.480
Clinging to the notion
that we need to maintain

20:34.481 --> 20:36.882
ready-alert ICBMs,

20:36.883 --> 20:39.218
that means STRATCOM has three minutes

20:39.219 --> 20:40.820
to make the call
to the crisis coordinator,

20:40.821 --> 20:42.054
who has two minutes

20:42.055 --> 20:43.856
to call the president.

20:43.857 --> 20:47.660
And then POTUS has five minutes
to make a decision.

20:47.661 --> 20:50.062
I mean, talk about vulnerability.

20:50.063 --> 20:51.731
It's insanity.

20:51.732 --> 20:53.366
After what happened today,

20:53.367 --> 20:55.868
how could we come
to any other conclusion?

20:55.869 --> 20:57.103
Maybe you should stay
in your lane, Elizabeth.

20:57.104 --> 20:58.337
Not if you're gonna blow up

20:58.338 --> 20:59.739
- the entire highway, Gordon.
- HILL: Okay, okay.

20:59.740 --> 21:02.608
Fine. Even if we got
the Russians to go along

21:02.609 --> 21:04.443
with the de-alerting,
there would be no way

21:04.444 --> 21:06.712
we could verify that they
were holding up their end.

21:06.713 --> 21:07.813
We verified START I and II.

21:07.814 --> 21:09.281
And what if there's a crisis

21:09.282 --> 21:10.716
and we have to go back on alert?

21:10.717 --> 21:13.119
A frenetic and unstable
re-alerting race

21:13.120 --> 21:16.122
could spiral into a launch.

21:16.123 --> 21:17.957
That threat could be managed.

21:17.958 --> 21:20.559
But forcing leaders
to make a snap decision

21:20.560 --> 21:23.596
about nuclear war with limited

21:23.597 --> 21:26.899
and hastily compiled
information is untenable.

21:26.900 --> 21:29.602
That's the game we're in,
and it's not gonna change.

21:29.603 --> 21:31.604
Why are you so dug in

21:31.605 --> 21:33.806
that you-you can't even see
another point of view?

21:33.807 --> 21:34.940
I'm not gonna argue.

21:34.941 --> 21:36.841
You're obviously having
an emotional reaction.

21:38.344 --> 21:41.781
Normally, I would have a
problem with a man telling me

21:41.782 --> 21:43.816
that I was emotional at work,

21:43.817 --> 21:44.984
but after what happened today,

21:44.985 --> 21:47.186
after thinking that I
was seeing my kids

21:47.187 --> 21:48.254
for the very last time,

21:48.255 --> 21:50.488
you are damn right I'm emotional.

21:51.524 --> 21:55.161
And maybe emotion is what's missing

21:55.162 --> 21:57.563
from the stupid, so-called logic

21:57.564 --> 22:01.400
behind our dehumanized
nuclear posture.

22:01.401 --> 22:04.103
You know what's even stupider?

22:04.104 --> 22:06.038
We've been here before.

22:06.039 --> 22:07.773
1979,

22:07.774 --> 22:10.141
like you alluded to,
only back then it was NORAD.

22:10.142 --> 22:11.784
They kicked it up to the NSA,

22:11.785 --> 22:13.786
who almost alerted Jimmy Carter

22:13.787 --> 22:17.723
because a simulation
was triggered between shifts.

22:17.724 --> 22:19.759
Talk about not learning a lesson.

22:19.760 --> 22:21.994
How many times today did we hear,

22:21.995 --> 22:24.797
"This can't be a mistake.
This can't be a mistake"?

22:24.798 --> 22:27.333
Meanwhile, satellites pick up

22:27.334 --> 22:29.990
a couple routine launches
practically every day,

22:29.991 --> 22:33.371
STRATCOM automatically starts
the drill in response,

22:33.372 --> 22:35.439
again and again, rinse and repeat.

22:35.440 --> 22:36.440
Bess is right.

22:36.441 --> 22:38.743
This-this is not

22:38.744 --> 22:41.278
a rational, deliberate process.

22:41.279 --> 22:45.149
It-it's the rote enactment
of a prepared script

22:45.150 --> 22:47.017
that forces leaders
to render decisions

22:47.018 --> 22:50.087
determining the fate
of the planet and mankind

22:50.088 --> 22:52.356
under excruciating pressure.

22:52.357 --> 22:55.726
If we, if we don't do
everything in our power

22:55.727 --> 23:00.931
to fix it, reduce the odds
of this happening again,

23:00.932 --> 23:04.702
then aren't we all complicit

23:04.703 --> 23:08.805
in recklessness
that borders on immorality?

23:24.889 --> 23:28.024
We'll talk again tomorrow.

23:35.213 --> 23:38.484
(GROANS) Russell hasn't
gotten back to me,

23:38.485 --> 23:39.785
and Emma is freaking out.

23:39.786 --> 23:41.821
God, she wants the whole guest list

23:41.822 --> 23:43.255
two months in advance; I mean, like,

23:43.256 --> 23:45.992
people lose their minds over weddings.

23:45.993 --> 23:47.493
ALISON: And what's with
Turks and Caicos?

23:47.494 --> 23:49.161
- Can you even afford that?
- STEVIE: No!

23:49.162 --> 23:51.030
I cannot, I can't eat out
for an entire month.

23:51.031 --> 23:52.565
It is very insensitive of her.

23:52.566 --> 23:54.533
- So blow it off.
- She's one of my best friends.

23:54.534 --> 23:55.701
I can't do that.

23:55.702 --> 23:57.169
You know, you guys,

23:57.170 --> 23:58.504
just go on, we got this.

23:58.505 --> 24:00.806
- Okay.
- Back to compulsively checking my blog.

24:00.807 --> 24:02.074
Oh, yeah,

24:02.075 --> 24:04.609
- when is your project due?
- Um, a week from Friday.

24:08.481 --> 24:10.483
I can't normalize.

24:10.484 --> 24:12.351
Me, either.

24:12.352 --> 24:14.853
How do we get our lives back?

24:16.122 --> 24:19.692
We just keep doing it, I guess.

24:19.693 --> 24:23.394
What were you thinking about,
when we were waiting?

24:24.130 --> 24:26.631
What a lucky man I am.

24:28.968 --> 24:31.370
What a blessed life I'd had.

24:31.371 --> 24:34.040
But sad, you know,

24:34.041 --> 24:36.876
for the kids, for the future
they wouldn't get to have.

24:36.877 --> 24:40.146
Me, too.

24:40.147 --> 24:43.214
(PHONE VIBRATES)

24:44.950 --> 24:47.252
(SIGHS SOFTLY)

24:49.855 --> 24:51.957
Conrad's here.

24:51.958 --> 24:55.294
I thought of telling Lydia,

24:55.295 --> 24:58.397
but she was washing her face,

24:58.398 --> 25:01.400
complaining about her crow's feet.

25:01.401 --> 25:05.604
I told her all I see
are those beautiful eyes,

25:05.605 --> 25:07.306
and she called me a liar.

25:07.307 --> 25:09.475
(LAUGHS SOFTLY)

25:09.476 --> 25:12.344
If only she knew how beautiful
she looked tonight.

25:12.345 --> 25:14.814
Ignorance really is bliss.

25:14.815 --> 25:16.716
Whole country.

25:16.717 --> 25:18.751
World.

25:18.752 --> 25:20.686
Oblivious.

25:20.687 --> 25:21.854
HENRY: Well.

25:21.855 --> 25:25.257
We were all in that oblivion
for a little while,

25:25.258 --> 25:28.327
but now there's no going back.

25:28.328 --> 25:30.796
No, indeed.

25:30.797 --> 25:32.865
When I believed
the Russians had launched,

25:32.866 --> 25:34.900
I kept trying to understand why.

25:34.901 --> 25:36.802
I thought, if it's all going to hell,

25:36.803 --> 25:39.004
and I'm responsible for half of it,

25:39.005 --> 25:41.941
I should at least comprehend it.

25:41.942 --> 25:44.343
HENRY: And what did you come up with?

25:44.344 --> 25:46.112
Well, you're gonna laugh.

25:46.113 --> 25:47.580
And it's not the perfect analogue,

25:47.581 --> 25:50.082
Professor.

25:50.083 --> 25:52.451
That fable about
the scorpion and the frog.

25:52.452 --> 25:54.053
(BOTH CHUCKLE)

25:54.054 --> 25:55.454
Well, that sounds about right.

25:55.455 --> 25:56.722
I thought, well, we killed

25:56.723 --> 25:59.658
300 Russians in Syria last week.

25:59.659 --> 26:01.827
It must just be
President Salnikov's nature

26:01.828 --> 26:03.896
to retaliate
with everything they've got.

26:03.897 --> 26:05.097
I know it doesn't make sense,

26:05.098 --> 26:07.933
but that's what keeps
spinning in my mind.

26:07.934 --> 26:09.902
Things that don't make sense.

26:09.903 --> 26:12.571
Like what if these
missiles don't protect us

26:12.572 --> 26:16.742
nearly as much as they threaten us?

26:16.743 --> 26:18.310
We need to do everything we can

26:18.311 --> 26:21.313
to make sure
that our policies make sense,

26:21.314 --> 26:24.917
and if they don't,
we need to change them.

26:24.918 --> 26:26.919
I thought you wanted to sleep on it.

26:26.920 --> 26:28.354
I did.

26:28.355 --> 26:31.357
Until I realized I can't sleep
without doing something.

26:31.358 --> 26:33.325
Name it.

26:33.326 --> 26:37.062
Back channel with the Russians.

26:37.063 --> 26:42.434
I'm guessing they got a whiff
of our silo doors opening.

26:42.435 --> 26:45.504
If you can get any interest
in mutual de-alerting,

26:45.505 --> 26:48.374
maybe we push for a new treaty.

26:48.375 --> 26:51.744
I'll drink to that.

26:51.745 --> 26:53.879
Isn't it a little late to call Moscow?

26:53.880 --> 26:56.482
Avdonin is in the Caymans
at a banking conference...

26:56.483 --> 26:57.750
or money laundering.

26:57.751 --> 26:59.185
I want to back channel
right in front of him

26:59.186 --> 27:00.886
on this one.

27:00.887 --> 27:03.022
DAISY: <i>Hey, gang.</i>

27:03.023 --> 27:05.724
- Pass me that pitcher, and a straw.
- ALL: Hey.

27:05.725 --> 27:07.126
What news from the world?

27:07.127 --> 27:09.528
Same. Just cable news
continuously reporting

27:09.529 --> 27:11.463
on Marine One landing
on the golf course,

27:11.464 --> 27:14.400
Air Force One's mystery flight,
and high-level officials

27:14.401 --> 27:18.304
being whisked away
and all of a sudden, returned.

27:18.305 --> 27:20.005
Well, everyone at
the White House is saying

27:20.006 --> 27:21.507
that it was some kind of drill, so...

27:21.508 --> 27:24.476
For nuclear evacuation... also,
I have a friend at the Pentagon

27:24.477 --> 27:25.845
- saying it wasn't a drill.
- What?

27:25.846 --> 27:28.848
Hey, you were whisked away
from the tennis courts.

27:28.849 --> 27:30.749
That was a nanny thing.

27:30.750 --> 27:32.718
No, that wasn't your nanny face.

27:32.719 --> 27:35.154
Here's what I think.

27:35.155 --> 27:39.191
I think it wasn't a drill,
and Jay got whisked.

27:39.192 --> 27:42.528
Because he's on the list.

27:42.529 --> 27:44.129
What list?

27:44.130 --> 27:48.801
The list, dude, the-the people
that get taken to Mount Weather.

27:48.802 --> 27:51.136
It's an underground
city where they keep

27:51.137 --> 27:52.938
a small population going
for a couple of years.

27:52.939 --> 27:54.106
How do you know if you're on the list?

27:54.107 --> 27:55.541
Well, they tell you.

27:55.542 --> 27:58.277
For example, I know
I am not on the list, so...

27:58.278 --> 27:59.979
My skin will be melting off my bones

27:59.980 --> 28:01.447
along with all of you lovely people.

28:01.448 --> 28:02.514
Thanks.

28:02.515 --> 28:03.849
- You're welcome.
- (SNORTS)

28:03.850 --> 28:05.951
But you're-you're on it,
though, aren't you?

28:05.952 --> 28:07.419
I mean, come on, you can tell us.

28:07.420 --> 28:08.687
We're not gonna hold it against you.

28:08.688 --> 28:09.722
Can we change the subject?

28:09.723 --> 28:12.057
- Seriously. Seriously.
- Uh-oh.

28:12.058 --> 28:13.492
I knew it.

28:13.493 --> 28:15.427
I'm not saying I'm on the list.

28:15.428 --> 28:17.129
(LAUGHS)

28:17.130 --> 28:18.297
But let me, let me just tell you

28:18.298 --> 28:21.033
what that particular
privilege buys you.

28:21.034 --> 28:22.368
Mm-hmm. Tell him.

28:22.369 --> 28:23.769
You get whisked away, you do...

28:23.770 --> 28:25.004
Mm-hmm.

28:25.005 --> 28:27.973
...without saying good-bye
to your friends and family.

28:27.974 --> 28:30.876
And then, you get to be
in an underground bunker

28:30.877 --> 28:34.813
with generals and top government
brass for weeks or months,

28:34.814 --> 28:38.651
eating MREs and
drinking ionized water.

28:38.652 --> 28:40.019
You emerge

28:40.020 --> 28:44.757
after the radiation's
reduced to livable levels,

28:44.758 --> 28:47.660
at which point, you get to try

28:47.661 --> 28:49.795
to pick out your loved ones' bones

28:49.796 --> 28:53.599
from the rubble and ash.

28:53.600 --> 28:56.769
And then, you spend

28:56.770 --> 28:59.505
however many years

28:59.506 --> 29:02.107
running the bombed out husk

29:02.108 --> 29:07.012
of the former United States
government under martial law.

29:07.013 --> 29:11.182
That's not a list
that you want to be on.

29:16.689 --> 29:17.823
Have a good night.

29:17.824 --> 29:20.993
- Good night.
- Good night.

29:20.994 --> 29:23.095
He's definitely on the list.

29:23.096 --> 29:25.763
<i>(KNOCKING ON DOOR)</i>

29:28.934 --> 29:32.071
Secretary McCord.

29:32.072 --> 29:34.740
I was surprised to hear you
requested to meet

29:34.741 --> 29:37.476
after what happened
in Syria last week.

29:37.477 --> 29:41.113
The loss of life was tragic,

29:41.114 --> 29:44.850
and I am truly sorry
for the soldiers' families.

29:44.851 --> 29:46.418
But that's not why I'm here.

29:46.419 --> 29:50.122
Did you not get the message
that I declined this meeting?

29:50.123 --> 29:52.091
I did.

29:52.092 --> 29:55.760
Yet you flew over a thousand
miles just to come here anyway.

29:58.931 --> 30:02.701
How do you say, "This better be good."

30:02.702 --> 30:04.969
(EXHALES)

30:08.273 --> 30:11.577
We need to overhaul
our nuclear weapons posture.

30:11.578 --> 30:13.579
Oh, is that all?

30:13.580 --> 30:17.549
Specifically, the hair trigger.

30:17.550 --> 30:21.286
Alert status, you call it
boy-eh-voy stat-tohs.

30:21.287 --> 30:23.655
Curious timing.

30:23.656 --> 30:26.825
GRU reported an interesting
military exercise

30:26.826 --> 30:30.429
your country performed yesterday.

30:30.430 --> 30:32.731
(SIGHS)

30:32.732 --> 30:36.368
Well, let's just say,

30:36.369 --> 30:40.072
made a compelling argument
for de-alerting.

30:40.073 --> 30:43.941
You must have had quite a day.

30:47.346 --> 30:48.747
I can get another one.

30:48.748 --> 30:50.983
No, thanks.

30:50.984 --> 30:54.520
All I'm asking is if you think

30:54.521 --> 30:57.189
there might be
an opening for a new treaty.

30:57.190 --> 30:59.491
De-alerting.

30:59.492 --> 31:02.528
Maybe even reducing stockpiles.

31:02.529 --> 31:06.531
We cherish our children
as much as you do, Elizabeth.

31:08.267 --> 31:12.471
This... this is an initial proposal

31:12.472 --> 31:14.906
for a framework.

31:17.810 --> 31:21.512
We could... even start now.

31:31.090 --> 31:32.591
Gordon Becker, ma'am.

31:32.592 --> 31:35.027
I heard about your little jaunt
to the Caymans.

31:35.028 --> 31:38.063
Well, yeah, I alerted your office.

31:38.064 --> 31:39.965
And... coffee?

31:39.966 --> 31:42.101
You're giving the
president bad advice.

31:42.102 --> 31:44.736
Well, isn't that for him to decide?

31:44.737 --> 31:46.505
I know you're the Dalton whisperer,

31:46.506 --> 31:47.739
but now you're getting into just...

31:47.740 --> 31:49.341
Excuse me, what?

31:49.342 --> 31:50.776
Oh, come on, Elizabeth.

31:50.777 --> 31:52.778
Everybody knows you play
the friend card with him.

31:52.779 --> 31:54.145
Really?

31:56.115 --> 31:57.249
I'm just trying to decide

31:57.250 --> 31:59.885
if that's more insulting
to me or POTUS.

31:59.886 --> 32:02.221
Look, I've never balked at
your out-of-the-box ideas

32:02.222 --> 32:03.589
when it comes to diplomacy,

32:03.590 --> 32:05.724
but now you're infringing
on national security.

32:05.725 --> 32:08.827
Well, as a member of
the National Security Council,

32:08.828 --> 32:11.763
I fail to see how
I'm infringing on anything.

32:11.764 --> 32:15.167
You are threatening
long-standing security policy.

32:15.168 --> 32:16.702
Threatening?

32:16.703 --> 32:20.172
If questioning how things
have been done is threatening,

32:20.173 --> 32:22.741
- doesn't that tell you something?
- Fine.

32:22.742 --> 32:26.445
I'm happy to authorize
a thorough feasibility review.

32:26.446 --> 32:28.280
Feasibility of what?

32:28.281 --> 32:31.283
No one questions that we can de-alert.

32:31.284 --> 32:33.819
There's nothing not feasible about it.

32:33.820 --> 32:36.221
I think we need to study that.

32:36.222 --> 32:38.290
You mean jam it up.

32:38.291 --> 32:41.593
And kill any hope of passage
in the Senate,

32:41.594 --> 32:45.129
where there is literally
an ICBM caucus.

32:45.864 --> 32:47.733
Politics ain't beanbag.

32:47.734 --> 32:50.302
No. No, it ain't.

32:50.303 --> 32:53.338
So what's it gonna take
to move you on this, Gordon?

32:53.339 --> 32:55.440
I mean, how can we work together

32:55.441 --> 32:58.576
to make this world
a safer place for our kids?

32:59.311 --> 33:01.046
Our kids are safest

33:01.047 --> 33:04.383
when we maintain the most
robust deterrent possible

33:04.384 --> 33:05.450
to Russian aggression.

33:05.451 --> 33:07.352
Look what happened last week in Syria.

33:07.353 --> 33:10.022
They saw weakness in our
relationship with Turkey,

33:10.023 --> 33:11.623
and not 24 hours later,

33:11.624 --> 33:14.059
they were exploiting it
to attack our troops.

33:14.060 --> 33:16.228
But is a regional dust-up
really comparable

33:16.229 --> 33:18.463
to what happened yesterday?

33:18.464 --> 33:22.401
Giving up even a shred
of strategic advantage...

33:22.402 --> 33:24.336
I'll never get behind it.

33:24.337 --> 33:27.872
After decades in the Pentagon,
that's just where I am.

33:28.640 --> 33:31.242
You need to let this go.

33:34.479 --> 33:36.847
♪

33:39.284 --> 33:42.754
ALISON: I totally need
to change my project.

33:42.755 --> 33:44.957
I need at least
50 likes on my blog post

33:44.958 --> 33:46.959
to qualify, and I'm at 28.

33:46.960 --> 33:48.927
What is wrong with people?

33:48.928 --> 33:50.896
Uh, they don't care about ponchos.

33:50.897 --> 33:52.048
That's my first guess.

33:52.049 --> 33:54.366
STEVIE: Russell Jackson
is ruining my life.

33:54.367 --> 33:56.235
I have texted him twice
and e-mailed once

33:56.236 --> 33:57.703
about Emma's wedding... radio silence.

33:57.704 --> 34:00.305
I mean, what else
am I supposed to be doing?!

34:00.306 --> 34:02.241
Maybe just give him a few more days.

34:02.242 --> 34:05.143
I just feel like he could
show me the respect

34:05.144 --> 34:06.645
of a one-word response.

34:06.646 --> 34:08.880
You know? Like, come on,
other people have lives.

34:08.880 --> 34:10.782
Oh, for Pete's sake, Stevie,
the man's busy.

34:10.783 --> 34:12.583
He has a lot more on his mind

34:12.585 --> 34:14.820
than your spoiled friend's
Caribbean wedding.

34:14.821 --> 34:17.755
Okay, Mom might be just
a little bit over-carbed.

34:17.757 --> 34:20.058
We're gonna take a time out.

34:20.059 --> 34:21.460
Come on.

34:21.460 --> 34:23.629
ELIZABETH: <i>They gotta hand it to me,</i>

34:23.630 --> 34:25.931
first real snap
since this whole thing started.

34:25.931 --> 34:28.634
- Okay, what's going on?
- You mean, other than seeing

34:28.635 --> 34:31.069
my life go up in a nuclear flash?

34:31.070 --> 34:33.938
- Uh... yeah, other than that.
- (SIGHS)

34:39.077 --> 34:41.947
Gordon and Ellen are still against...

34:41.947 --> 34:44.349
taking our nukes off the hair trigger.

34:44.350 --> 34:46.385
Even with Russian cooperation.

34:46.386 --> 34:48.186
- (SIGHS)
- I mean, it's like

34:48.187 --> 34:50.054
I went and I got the witch's broom

34:50.056 --> 34:53.025
and the Wizard still
won't send me home.

34:53.025 --> 34:55.661
I... Now I understand why
they call the inner sanctum

34:55.661 --> 34:59.631
at the Pentagon the "priesthood".

34:59.632 --> 35:03.068
Our nuclear stance is,
like, their dogma.

35:03.069 --> 35:05.904
Even the most stodgy
religious institutions

35:05.905 --> 35:07.606
can change with time.

35:07.607 --> 35:09.708
Yeah, well, we don't have that.

35:09.709 --> 35:10.942
And the Catholic Church

35:10.943 --> 35:13.512
was never in danger
of blowing up the world

35:13.513 --> 35:15.247
while they were evolving. It's...

35:15.248 --> 35:17.316
Okay, let's use the Socratic method.

35:17.317 --> 35:19.951
- Oh, please.
- How do you get both the Church

35:19.952 --> 35:23.121
and the government to change
their position on anything?

35:23.122 --> 35:25.190
I don't... I don't know.

35:25.191 --> 35:27.392
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

35:27.393 --> 35:29.193
Popular demand.

35:30.162 --> 35:32.664
And where does
popular demand come from?

35:32.665 --> 35:34.833
You mean other than the people?

35:34.834 --> 35:36.435
Why did the Protestant
Reformation happen?

35:36.436 --> 35:37.969
Hurry this up, Socrates.

35:37.970 --> 35:39.338
The printing press.

35:39.339 --> 35:43.141
Putting the Bible
into the hands of the people.

35:43.142 --> 35:47.378
The Church couldn't control
the information anymore.

35:48.413 --> 35:50.414
Declassify.

35:51.183 --> 35:53.185
If you want to change
our nuclear policy,

35:53.186 --> 35:55.220
you need the people on your side.

35:55.221 --> 35:58.724
To get them, you need
to tell them how close we came.

35:58.725 --> 36:01.626
♪

36:01.627 --> 36:03.595
RUSSELL: <i>Why the hell</i>

36:03.596 --> 36:05.664
would we declassify any of it?

36:05.665 --> 36:07.199
(SIGHS) Because sunlight

36:07.200 --> 36:08.967
is the best disinfectant.

36:08.968 --> 36:12.104
Yes, and it causes cancer, too.

36:12.105 --> 36:14.773
Sir, I am convinced that the only way

36:14.774 --> 36:17.042
to move the Senate on de-alerting

36:17.043 --> 36:19.444
is to bring the public into it.

36:19.445 --> 36:22.547
- By scaring the crap out of them.
- Yes, exactly.

36:22.548 --> 36:24.850
The secrecy has...

36:24.851 --> 36:28.420
lulled everybody into this
false sense of security.

36:28.421 --> 36:30.389
It's time we wake 'em up.

36:30.390 --> 36:32.424
Then they'll pressure
their senators, you think,

36:32.425 --> 36:34.526
into, uh, getting on board
with de-alerting?

36:34.527 --> 36:35.431
I do.

36:35.432 --> 36:38.096
<i>Or</i> it'll be a black eye
on this administration.

36:38.097 --> 36:39.164
Hmm.

36:39.165 --> 36:41.133
Hell, it could put us in traction,

36:41.134 --> 36:45.036
giving more ammo to our already
considerable opposition in Congress,

36:45.037 --> 36:47.372
and you'll be the lamest lame duck

36:47.373 --> 36:48.540
in history, sir.

36:48.541 --> 36:49.908
So release it all.

36:49.909 --> 36:51.877
Every...

36:51.878 --> 36:53.912
false alarm, glitch and close call

36:53.913 --> 36:57.048
all the way back to the '50s,
including by the Russians.

36:57.049 --> 36:59.718
And the priesthood will buckle.

36:59.719 --> 37:01.520
Well, certainly those in the Senate

37:01.521 --> 37:04.021
worried about the next election.

37:05.657 --> 37:07.559
I say yeah.

37:07.560 --> 37:10.461
Let's scare the crap out of America.

37:17.007 --> 37:19.410
- 35 seconds, Mr. President.
- Thank you, Amy.

37:19.411 --> 37:20.966
Lock it up, everyone.

37:20.967 --> 37:23.602
- 30 seconds.
- Well...

37:23.603 --> 37:25.770
- any second thoughts?
- (SIGHS): Always.

37:25.771 --> 37:29.241
But... it's a bold move, sir.

37:29.242 --> 37:32.277
Hey, I, uh, heard you're
working on a model airplane.

37:32.278 --> 37:34.913
- Corsair.
- From who?

37:34.914 --> 37:36.114
15 seconds.

37:36.115 --> 37:37.315
If you could please have
a seat, Mr. President.

37:37.316 --> 37:38.583
Break a leg, sir.

37:38.584 --> 37:41.119
Are we sure this is
the right color tie?

37:41.120 --> 37:42.387
(MAN CHUCKLES)

37:42.388 --> 37:45.489
And five, four, three...

37:47.425 --> 37:50.428
Good evening, my fellow Americans.

37:50.429 --> 37:52.864
I want to share with you
a crisis that unfolded

37:52.865 --> 37:54.099
this past Saturday.

37:54.100 --> 37:57.435
Fortunately, it was resolved
with no harm done,

37:57.436 --> 38:01.206
but as stakeholders in our
nation's safety and security,

38:01.207 --> 38:03.575
you deserve to know what happened.

38:03.576 --> 38:07.546
At 10:48 in the morning,
I was informed that Russia

38:07.547 --> 38:10.181
had launched a massive nuclear attack

38:10.182 --> 38:11.816
against the United States.

38:11.817 --> 38:14.853
Every indication was that it was real

38:14.854 --> 38:17.255
and would strike in 20 minutes.

38:17.256 --> 38:19.658
My fellow citizens...

38:19.659 --> 38:23.093
I ordered an equally
massive counterattack.

38:24.563 --> 38:26.298
NEWSWOMAN: <i>After weeks of protest</i>

38:26.299 --> 38:28.833
<i>in the U.S. and around the globe,</i>

38:28.834 --> 38:31.002
the United States and Russia
have agreed to a treaty

38:31.003 --> 38:33.838
to take their ICBMs
off hair-trigger alert.

38:33.839 --> 38:37.542
Seeing the overwhelming popular
support for the new policy,

38:37.543 --> 38:39.611
a supermajority of U.S. senators

38:39.612 --> 38:41.913
have signaled
they will ratify the treaty,

38:41.914 --> 38:43.949
which would also draw
clear parameters...

38:43.950 --> 38:46.985
U.S.-India Strategic
and Commercial Dialogue Support

38:46.986 --> 38:48.653
for local female entrepreneurs

38:48.654 --> 38:50.755
manufacturing sea salt in Indonesia.

38:50.756 --> 38:52.157
Fact-checked and footnoted,

38:52.158 --> 38:55.527
with alphabetical headings
and subheadings.

38:55.528 --> 38:57.262
(WHISPERS): Boom.

38:57.263 --> 38:59.698
I say "boom" sometimes.

38:59.699 --> 39:01.800
No, I'm just... I am staggered

39:01.801 --> 39:04.135
by your speed and persistence.

39:04.136 --> 39:06.437
Well, they're my superpowers.

39:07.005 --> 39:09.040
(LAUGHS) Good job.

39:09.041 --> 39:12.443
All right, go, go, go.
Go have a Saturday.

39:14.546 --> 39:16.081
(CLEARS THROAT)

39:16.082 --> 39:17.582
What's up?

39:17.583 --> 39:19.483
I want more.

39:20.619 --> 39:22.821
Oh, my God, you're one of us.

39:22.822 --> 39:24.189
Okay, um...

39:24.190 --> 39:26.758
earthquake resilience
development in Turkmenistan.

39:26.759 --> 39:28.059
Boom.

39:28.060 --> 39:29.427
Come on, Waffles.

39:29.428 --> 39:31.830
Come on. Let's get a break.

39:31.831 --> 39:34.065
MAN: Hey, is that a beagle?

39:34.066 --> 39:35.166
Sure is.

39:35.167 --> 39:38.336
- Rumor is his parents were show dogs.
- (LAUGHS)

39:38.337 --> 39:40.672
You get him, uh, from a breeder?

39:40.673 --> 39:42.073
No, he's a rescue.

39:42.074 --> 39:44.142
I've been thinking of doing that.

39:44.143 --> 39:45.909
How's it working out?

39:46.678 --> 39:49.747
Well, so far, so good.

39:50.782 --> 39:52.250
JAY: <i>Right where we left off.</i>

39:52.251 --> 39:53.885
One-four, my serve.

39:53.886 --> 39:56.721
Man, I can't even believe
I got a point off of you,

39:56.722 --> 39:59.224
- let alone, what, four games?
- Will you stop?

39:59.225 --> 40:01.393
You're going down.
I hope you're hungry,

40:01.394 --> 40:03.260
- 'cause you're gonna eat this.
- Let's go.

40:04.129 --> 40:05.964
<i>(VIDEO GAME TIRES SCREECH)</i>

40:05.965 --> 40:07.432
ALISON: See, Dad?

40:07.433 --> 40:09.167
Once you got over the
not-crashing phase,

40:09.168 --> 40:10.201
you're unstoppable.

40:10.202 --> 40:12.003
I love crashing. It's my thing.

40:12.004 --> 40:13.938
Okay, well, the game's not over yet.

40:13.939 --> 40:15.640
STEVIE: All but the crying.

40:15.641 --> 40:17.909
He's <i>five laps</i> ahead.

40:17.910 --> 40:19.577
Okay, I'm making nachos.

40:19.578 --> 40:22.313
Ooh, yes, please. And guacamole.

40:22.314 --> 40:24.282
I am only one person.

40:24.283 --> 40:26.351
(GROANS) Okay, I'll chop and shred.

40:26.352 --> 40:29.421
- You mean like I'm doing right now?
- Oh, okay, yeah, keep it up.

40:29.422 --> 40:31.456
They did a nice job of sodding over

40:31.457 --> 40:33.291
where Marine One landed.

40:33.292 --> 40:35.226
Almost like it never happened.

40:35.227 --> 40:38.063
(CHUCKLES): Yeah. Almost.

40:38.064 --> 40:40.298
Take it, uh...

40:40.299 --> 40:44.002
Gordon and Ellen bowed
politely out of the game?

40:44.003 --> 40:46.071
Quite politely. (CHUCKLES)

40:46.072 --> 40:48.473
They're still stinging
over de-alerting, but...

40:48.474 --> 40:51.376
they'll come around.

40:51.377 --> 40:55.213
I am just grateful to play
a quiet round of golf

40:55.214 --> 40:58.717
without worrying about nuclear winter.

40:58.718 --> 41:02.087
Not that it
can't happen anyway, but...

41:02.088 --> 41:04.022
at least we, uh,

41:04.023 --> 41:06.958
turned the odds
significantly in our favor.

41:06.959 --> 41:09.260
(CHUCKLES): Bess...

41:09.261 --> 41:12.597
you want to go ahead
and put him out of his bliss?

41:12.598 --> 41:15.599
Well, actually,
I'm a little rusty, but...

41:20.472 --> 41:21.406
Huh.

41:21.407 --> 41:22.507
<i>I let the president win.</i>

41:22.508 --> 41:23.875
HENRY: <i>Smart.</i>

41:23.876 --> 41:26.611
Russell I hammered.

41:26.612 --> 41:29.714
(CHUCKLES): Good for you.

41:29.715 --> 41:32.283
So, what's this return visit about?

41:32.284 --> 41:35.920
Sort of a... full-circle celebration?

41:35.921 --> 41:38.757
Sorta. It just...

41:38.758 --> 41:41.258
felt appropriate.

41:42.894 --> 41:46.030
This whole ordeal has reminded me

41:46.031 --> 41:49.867
about the importance of civic duty.

41:50.869 --> 41:55.473
It's reaffirmed my faith
in the process, you know?

41:55.474 --> 41:57.441
I do.

42:00.145 --> 42:02.380
We got this enormous
thing done, Henry,

42:02.381 --> 42:04.616
and I feel a responsibility

42:04.617 --> 42:07.652
to make sure it doesn't get undone.

42:07.653 --> 42:10.320
When the time comes...

42:11.689 --> 42:14.292
...I want to run for president.

42:14.293 --> 42:16.361
I know.

42:16.362 --> 42:18.395
- You do?
- Mm-hmm.

42:19.130 --> 42:22.232
Wow. I really didn't.

42:24.369 --> 42:27.939
But that's nothing new.

42:27.940 --> 42:31.276
There's one other thing I know.

42:31.277 --> 42:33.277
I'm with you.

